23/10/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- An international co-ordination centre to fight money counterfeiting is to open in Bulgaria, said Eduard Liedgens, the euro co-ordinator of the Bavarian police force.
He met on Wednesday (22 October) with Bulgarian Interior Ministry Chief Secretary Boyko Borissov and Chief Prosecutor Nikola Filchev.
Liedgens said the centre would pool and analyse data from the special security services of all EU countries.
In other news, Indian President Abdul Kalam arrived in Sofia on Wednesday.
He will sign a number of co-operation accords on criminal extradition, youth sports and IT trade.
(24 Chassa, Trud, Dnevnik - 23/10/03;
BTA, BNT - 22/10/03)
